To compile dcraw for Windows or Mac OS X follow the steps below, note that
for Linux the dcraw package should be installed instead.

Mac OS X:
- Make sure XCode is installed and start a terminal.

- Extract the dcraw sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- Compile dcraw using:
  gcc -DNO_JPEG -DNO_LCMS -DDJGPP -O3 -mtune=generic -march=i686 -mmmx -msse -msse2 -mfpmath=sse -o dcraw dcraw.c

- Copy the dcraw file to ext/exif/bin.macx.

Windows:
- Make sure MinGW and MSYS are installed and start a MinGW bash shell.

- Extract the dcraw sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- Compile dcraw using:
  gcc -DNO_JPEG -DNO_LCMS -DDJGPP -O3 -mtune=generic -march=i686 -mmmx -msse -msse2 -mfpmath=sse -mincoming-stack-boundary=2 -o dcraw.exe dcraw.c -lws2_32
  
- Copy the dcraw.exe file to ext/dcraw/bin.win32.
